  "text": "Effects of bacterial products on the cyclic GMP levels in rat aortic rings. Rat aortic rings were incubated for 4 h with saline (Control [Ct]), RGPs (10 g/ml), LTA (10 g/ml), or LPS (10 g/ml) alone (open bars) or with L-NAME (1 mmol/liter; closed bars). The cyclic GMP content of tissue was measured at t 8 h after the first contact with bacterial components. ‫,ء‬ P Ͻ 0.05, and ‫,ءء‬ P Ͻ 0.01 compared with controls; ն, P Ͻ 0.05, and նն, P Ͻ 0.01 compared with the same treatment but without L-NAME (n ϭ 9). the contractile effect of NA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . All of these effects are inhibited by an inhibitor of NO synthase or by dexamethasone, which prevents the induction of i-NOS in the vascular wall [CITATION_3] .",
